  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nThe component `quo2.components.community.community-list-view` doesn't fully support the [Figma specs](https://www.figma.com/file/WQZcp6S0EnzxdTL4taoKDv/Design-System-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=8917-153680&mode=design&t=As17D4fdkFcWD3Gl-0) for the component `List items` > `Community List`.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/46027/abc97f23-6c32-40ad-820c-71ebe1dac73e\" width=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\n- Consider re-implementing the component to better match the component properties specified in Figma, or try to match the Figma properties 1:1 with the Clojure code. Right now the component is tied to the *community entity*, but the Figma component has quite different property names. This confuses devs while reviewing the component. It's a general problem of many of the quo2 components and it has been recently reported by @J-Son89. Just one practical example.\r\n- Rewrite the component to follow the guidelines because it's outdated.\r\n\r\n### Out of scope\r\n\r\n- The quo2 component has 2 usages, such as [this one](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/blob/bca7ab7925269545aa1e9a141fb809dd218877d6/src/status_im2/contexts/communities/home/view.cljs#L30). They will need to be updated, but we should preferably do it in a separate issue.\r\n- The component *usage* has bugs, e.g. the community map has a key `:muted`, but the `quo2` component expects a `muted?`, so in the end, the muted state isn't displayed in the Communities home screen.\r\n\r\n### Comparison\r\n\r\nTo resolve this issue, implement all possible variations specified in Figma and update the preview area.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/46027/f5c14037-b62c-4881-bf8d-426c411a78b5\" width=\"400\" />",
